                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>New York 144 Thompson St.</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <date>Oct 13<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 5612</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Dear Sir/</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I missed you at the consecration of our<lb/> new\n                                        synagogue. I believe had you been present you<lb/> would\n                                        have been pleased with the ceremony. I enclose<lb/> you a\n                                        Book containing the form of service for the<lb/> occasion,\n                                        and will also give you a short description<lb/> in the way\n                                        of criticism upon the whole according to the<lb/> best of my\n                                                  <sic>judgement</sic>. The Building I am told is\n                                        Gothic<lb/> but as I do not understand architectural terms I\n                                        will not<lb/> attempt a description of it, it is however\n                                        according to my<lb/> taste the most beautiful synagogue I\n                                        have ever seen. It<lb/> is yet in an unfinished state this\n                                        in a measure marred<lb/> the effect on the day of\n                                        consecration yet still under this<lb/> great disadvantage it\n                                        was a most beautiful picture, the<lb/> Ladies Gallery was so\n                                                  <sic>crouded</sic> that it was found\n                                        necessary<lb/> to seat many <del>Ladies</del> below in the\n                                        body of the building<lb/> which was very full without being\n                                                  <sic>crouded</sic>. The Mayor<lb/> and authorities\n                                        of the city were all present But the<lb/>\n                                        <add>חזנים</add> of the synagogues various (who were all\n                                        invited) were nearly<lb/> all absent. I however noticed that\n                                                  <persName>Doctor Lilienthal</persName> was<lb/>\n                                        there. The orchestra which were composed of the most<lb/>\n                                        eminent Professional men in the city was truly\n                                        beautiful<lb/> the opening symphony or overture called\n                                        Joseph composed<lb/> by <persName>Mehul</persName> was most\n                                        splendidly performed. The chorus<lb/> composed of Boys &amp;\n                                        men numbering 25 were exceedingly well</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34747b7x/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
