                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>drilled and performed their parts admirably—the six<lb/> first\n                                                  <add>מזמורים</add> were all <sic>chaunted</sic> by\n                                        me which was not<lb/> according to my original intention as\n                                        each <add>חזן</add> had been<lb/> presented with a\n                                                  <add>מזמור</add> but as they were not present\n                                        I<lb/> was obliged to undertake the whole. The\n                                                  <sic>chaunting</sic> was<lb/> in the old style by\n                                        verse and next verse <del>answered</del> by chorus<lb/>\n                                        accompanied by the organ until the few concluding\n                                        verses<lb/> which were sang by the <add>in the old style by\n                                                  חזן verse and next verse</add> to original music\n                                        composed<lb/> by my Brother <persName>Louis Leo</persName>\n                                        of <placeName>London</placeName>—accompanied either by<lb/>\n                                        the organ or the Band. The 7<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi>\n                                        <add>חזן</add> was arranged<lb/> as a Trio—sang by\n                                                  <persName>Mr Lichtenstein</persName>\n                                        <persName>Master Hecht</persName> and<lb/>\n                                                  myself—<add>מזמור</add> was sang by myself and\n                                        chorus<lb/> accompanied by the full band—next came\n                                                  <persName>Dr <sic>Raphhalls</sic></persName><lb/>\n                                        sermon (no doubt you have seen it published as a composition\n                                        of its merit<lb/> I will not speak but it occupied too long\n                                        a time and<lb/> the long prayer composed by the late\n                                                  <persName>Dr Herschel</persName> read in<lb/>\n                                        Hebrew by the Doctor and the long list of Donations<lb/>\n                                        which amounted to nearly $2000 so completely tired<lb/> the\n                                        congregation that many left—next came that<lb/> splendid\n                                        composition of the late <persName>professor\n                                                  Harwitz</persName> one<lb/> verse of which was\n                                        adapted by <persName>Dr Raphall</persName> for the<lb/>\n                                        occasion—next the <add>מזמור לדוד</add> sung by me\n                                        accompanied by the<lb/> full orchestra, and the Finale\n                                                  <add>נותן תשועה</add> by the chorus<lb/> and full\n                                        orchestra—the whole occupied about<lb/> three hours and a\n                                        half and I suppose the sermon<lb/> the prayer &amp; the\n                                                  <add>הללויה</add> occupied at least 2 hours<lb/>\n                                        and ¼ this great length of the sermon &amp;c &amp;c\n                                        added<lb/> to the one hours delay before commencing was\n                                        the<lb/> only reasonable fault that could be found with\n                                        the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34747b7x/canvas/p2"
