                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34747b7x/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>ceremony. Upon the whole the congregation were<lb/> highly\n                                        delighted, and I rec<hi rend=\"sup\">d</hi> many flattering\n                                        compliments<lb/> from members as well as strangers for the\n                                        manner<lb/> in which I had <sic>superinteded</sic> the\n                                        whole—the Gentlemen<lb/> of the orchestra were delighted\n                                        with the music<lb/> composed by my Brother who wrote it\n                                        about 20<lb/> years ago for the consecration of the London\n                                        Synagogue<lb/> in <placeName>St Albans Place,\n                                                  Haymarket</placeName>, where my late Father<lb/>\n                                        was <add>מי שברך</add> the ode by the late\n                                                  <persName>Professor Hurwitz</persName> was\n                                        also<lb/> written for the same occasion.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Trustees being impressed by the great\n                                        labor<lb/> I had in getting up this ceremony presented<lb/>\n                                        me with a very liberal sum of money as a<lb/> mark of their\n                                        approbation for the service I had<lb/> rendered them.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">This my dear Sir is a rough sketch which<lb/> you\n                                        can make use of or not just as it suits<lb/> you—and if you\n                                        please to insert the<lb/> particulars in the Occident rest\n                                        assured<lb/> there is no exaggeration or prejudice in<lb/>\n                                        any one of the facts stated</p>\n                              <p>Trusting that this will find you in excellent<lb/> health</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">I am Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">yours faithfully</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Ansel Leo</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>To</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">&amp;c &amp;c &amp;c</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34747b7x/canvas/p3"
                }
